C. Average Throughput The average throughput characteristics are shown in Fig. 9.
The Ô¨Ågure shows that the throughput is improved by the proposed method when the number of LoRa nodes is small. By contrast, when the number of LoRa nodes is large, the throughput is slightly lower than that of the conventional method. This is because smaller DC are used in the proposed method in order to guarantee the required packet loss rate. Considering both the allowable interference time ratio and the required packet loss rate results in decreasing the DC of each LoRa. As a result, the throughput is also decreased.

